rComments: Awesome professor, very friendly, funny, approachable.  One of the best classes I have ever taken at U of I.  Excellent professor.  Highly recommend taking the class and meeting him.

Who said he was hot?  He's not attractive, but he's a great professor!  Dr. Notaro is the man!  He's so funny and he actually makes stats interesting!  I went to every class so I wouldn't miss his football predictions!  He is awesome and I would definitely take another class taught by him!
Always funny, loves his students, GREAT teacher, and a snappy dresser!
If you hate math like me don't let this class scare you away because the hw is easy and you get 4 pages to write notes on for the tests. I never studied and got an A.

what a great class.  gotta love his quirky humor... he keeps things interesting and his exams (and homework) are pretty easy.  think 4-pages front and back of notes to take into the exam.  TAKE THIS CLASS!

This class was great. Dr. Notaro is an awesome professor who is very interested in what he teaches, and it shows. Medical ethics is a class that makes you think about what health issues are going on in the world.
This class is very easy. He's an overall good teacher, his classes seem to be pretty easy.
I thought he was a nice person and an ok teacher, but had a very wierd sense of humor.  His personality was a bit odd, but he was a nice man.
A very cool professor.  Ask a question on the midterm such as "So what IS the class you are taking?"
This guy is a ****.  Props to you dude.  You are the man.  Teachers don't get cooler than this.
